\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\begin_inset Marginal
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
A well-balanced line width improves the legibility of the text.
 That's what typography is all about, right?
\end_layout

\end_inset

Many theses, some books, and several other publications have been typeset
 successfully with classic thesis.
 If you are interested in typographic details behind it, enjoy Robert Bringhurst
's wonderful book.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Important Note:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some things of this style might look unusual at first glance, many people
 feel so in the beginning.
 However, all things are intentionally designed to be as they are, especially
 these: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
No bold fonts are used.
 Italics or spaced small caps do the job quite well.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The size of the text body is intentionally shaped like it is.
 It supports both legibility and allows a reasonable amount of information
 to be on a page.
 And, no: the lines are not too short.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The tables intentionally do not use vertical or double rules.
 See the documentation for the 
\family typewriter
booktabs
\family default
 package for a nice discussion of this topic.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
To be found online at 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Flex URL
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

http://www.ctan.org/tex-archive/macros/latex/contrib/booktabs/
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
And last but not least, to provide the reader with a way easier access to
 page numbers in the table of contents, the page numbers are right behind
 the titles.
 Yes, they are 
\emph on
not
\emph default
 neatly aligned at the right side and they are 
\emph on
not
\emph default
 connected with dots that help the eye to bridge a distance that is not
 necessary.
 If you are still not convinced: is your reader interested in the page number
 or does she want to sum the numbers up? 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, please do not break the beauty of the style by changing these
 things unless you really know what you are doing! Please.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Another Important Note:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since the first release of 
\family typewriter
classic\SpecialChar softhyphen
the\SpecialChar softhyphen
sis
\family default
 in 2006, many things have changed in the \SpecialChar LaTeX
 world.
  Trying to keep up-to-date, 
\family typewriter
classicthesis
\family default
 grew and evolved  into many directions, trying to stay stable and be  compatibl
e with its port to \SpecialChar LyX
.
 However, there are still many  remains from older times in the code, many
 dirty workarounds here and  there, and several other things I am absolutely
 not proud of (for  example my unwise combination of 
\size footnotesize
KOMA
\size default
-script and 
\family typewriter
titlesec
\family default
 etc.).
 
\begin_inset Marginal
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
 An outlook into the future of 
\family typewriter
classicthesis
\family default
.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Currently, I am looking into how to completely re-design and  re-implement
 
\family typewriter
classicthesis
\family default
 making it easier to maintain and use.
 As a general idea, 
\family typewriter
classicthesis.sty
\family default
 should be  distributed separately from the template  itself.
  Excellent spin-offs such as 
\family typewriter
arsclassica
\family default
 could also be  integrated (with permission of their authors) as format
 configurations.
  Also, current trends of 
\family typewriter
microtype
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
fontspec
\family default
, and others  should be included as well.
 As I am not really into deep  \SpecialChar LaTeX
 programming,  I will reach out to the \SpecialChar LaTeX
 community
 for their expertise and help.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Organization
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:Organization"

\end_inset

A very important factor for successful thesis writing is the organization
 of the material.
 This template suggests the structure as follows: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Marginal
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
You can use these margins for summaries of the text body
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
dots
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
Chapters/
\family default
 is where all the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

real
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 content goes in separate files such as 
\family typewriter
Chapter01.tex
\family default
 etc.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
FrontBackMatter/
\family default
 is where all the stuff goes that surrounds the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

real
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 content, such as the acknowledgments, dedication, etc.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
gfx/
\family default
 is where you put all the graphics you use in the thesis.
 Maybe they should be organized into subfolders depending on the chapter
 they are used in, if you have a lot of graphics.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
Bibliography.bib
\family default
: a  Bib\SpecialChar TeX
 database to organize all the references you might want to cite.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
classicthesis.sty
\family default
: the style definition to get this awesome look and feel.
 Does not only work with this thesis template but also on its own (see folder
 
\family typewriter
Examples
\family default
).
 Bonus: works with \SpecialChar LaTeX
, 
\shape smallcaps
pdf
\shape default
\SpecialChar LaTeX
, 
\shape smallcaps
xe
\shape default
\SpecialChar LaTeX
, 
\shape smallcaps
lua
\shape default
\SpecialChar LaTeX
\SpecialChar ldots
 and all of them from \SpecialChar LyX
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
ClassicThesis.tex
\family default
: the main file of your thesis where all gets bundled together.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
classicthesis-config.tex
\family default
: a central place to load all nifty packages that are used.
 
\emph on

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Make your changes and adjustments here.

\emph default
 This means that you specify here the options you want to load 
\family typewriter
classicthesis.sty
\family default
 with.
 You also adjust the title of your thesis, your name, and all similar informatio
n here.
 Refer to 
\begin_inset Flex CT - auto cross-reference
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand labelonly
reference "sec:customization"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

 for more information.
 
\end_layout

