\begin_layout Section
Style Options
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:options"

\end_inset

There are a couple of options for 
\family typewriter
classicthesis.sty
\family default
 that allow for a bit of freedom concerning the layout: 
\begin_inset Marginal
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Options are enabled via 
\family typewriter
option=true
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
General: 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
drafting
\family default
: prints the date and time at the bottom of each page, so you always know
 which version you are dealing with.
 Might come in handy not to give your Prof.
 that old draft.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Parts and Chapters: 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
parts
\family default
: use this option if you 
\emph on
need
\emph default
 Part divisions in your document.
 This is necessary to get the spacing of the Table of Contents right.
 (Cannot be used together with 
\family typewriter
nochapters
\family default
.) 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
nochapters
\family default
: allows to use the classicthesis style with classes that do not use chapters,
 e.
\begin_inset space \thinspace{}
\end_inset

g., for articles.
 Automatically turns off a couple of other options: 
\family typewriter
eulerchapternumbers
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
linedheaders
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
listsseparated
\family default
, and 
\family typewriter
parts
\family default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
linedheaders
\family default
: changes the look of the chapter headings a bit by adding a horizontal
 line above the chapter title.
 The chapter number will also be moved to the top of the page, above the
 chapter title.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Typography: 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
style
\family default
: this offers a convenient way of switching between different major styles.
 Default style is 
\family typewriter
classicthesis
\family default
.
 As a new feature, Lorenzo Pantieri's 
\family typewriter
arsclassica
\family default
 is available as well.
 With his permission, 
\family typewriter
classicthesis-arsclassica.sty
\family default
 is now part of 
\family typewriter
classicthesis
\family default
 and will be maintained here.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
palatino
\family default
: Hermann Zapf's classic font is the free standard font for this style.
 Robert Bringhurst's book uses Adobe's commercial font Minion Pro.
 However, there are other free alternatives also available.
 Deactivate this option for loading such alternatives and see 
\family typewriter
classicthesis-config.tex
\family default
 for some suggestions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
eulerchapternumbers
\family default
: use figures from Hermann Zapf's Euler math font for the chapter numbers.
 By default, old style figures from the Palatino font are used.
 This option only works with pdfLaTeX.
 XeTeX and LuaTeX will use different default options that can be easily
 changed by the user; check Font section of classicthesis.sty for details.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
beramono
\family default
: loads Bera Mono as a typewriter font.
 (Default setting is using the standard CM typewriter font.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
eulermath
\family default
: loads the awesome Euler fonts for math.
 Pala\SpecialChar softhyphen
tino is used as the default font.
 This option only works with pdfLaTeX.
 XeTeX and LuaTeX can easily be configured to use any font you want.
 
\begin_inset Note Comment
status open

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
pdfspacing
\family default
: makes use of pdf\SpecialChar TeX
 letter spacing capabilities via the 
\family typewriter
microtype
\family default
 package.
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Use 
\family typewriter
microtype
\family default
's 
\family typewriter
DVIoutput
\family default
 option to generate DVI with pdftex.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 This fixes some serious issues regarding math formulæ etc.
 (e.
\begin_inset space \thinspace{}
\end_inset

g., 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

ß
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

) in headers.
 This is an obsolete option, letterspacing will either be done by microtype
 or fontspec, depending on the engine used.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
minionprospacing
\family default
: uses the internal 
\family typewriter
textssc
\family default
 command of the 
\family typewriter
MinionPro
\family default
 package for letter spacing.
 This enables the 
\family typewriter
minionpro
\family default
 option and overrides 
\family typewriter
pdfspacing
\family default
.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Table of Contents: 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
tocaligned
\family default
: aligns the whole table of contents on the left side.
 Some people like that, some don't.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
dottedtoc
\family default
: sets pagenumbers flushed right in the table of contents.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
manychapters
\family default
: if you need more than nine chapters for your document, you might not be
 happy with the spacing between the chapter number and the chapter title
 in the Table of Contents.
 This option allows for additional space in this context.
 However, it does not look as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

perfect
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 if you use 
\family typewriter

\backslash
parts
\family default
 for structuring your document.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Floats: 
\begin_inset Separator latexpar
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
floatperchapter
\family default
: activates numbering per chapter for all floats such as figures, tables,
 and listings (if used).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
listings
\family default
: loads the 
\family typewriter
listings
\family default
 package and configures the List of Listings accordingly.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\family typewriter
subfig
\family default
: subfigure option is passed to the 
\family typewriter
tocloft
\family default
 package to enable compatibility with the 
\family typewriter
subfig
\family default
 package.
 Enable this option if you will use the package.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
Furthermore, pre-defined margins for different paper sizes are available,
 i.e.
 a4 paper, a5 paper, b5 paper, and letter paper.
 These are based on your chosen option of 
\family typewriter

\backslash
documentclass
\family default
.
 Both 
\family typewriter
paper=a4
\family default
 and 
\family typewriter
a4paper
\family default
 options will work.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The best way to figure these options out is to try different possibilities
 and see what you and your supervisor like best.
 To make things easier, 
\family typewriter
classicthesis\SpecialChar softhyphen
-config.tex
\family default
 contains some useful commands that might help you.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Customization
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:customization"

\end_inset

This section will give you a few hints about how to adapt 
\family typewriter
classicthesis
\family default
 to your needs.
 The file 
\family typewriter
classicthesis.sty
\family default
 contains the core functionality of the style and in most cases will be
 left intact, whereas 
\family typewriter
classicthesis-config.tex
\family default
 is used for some common user customizations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The first customization you are about to make is to alter the document title,
 author name, and other thesis details.
 In order to do this, replace the data in the following lines of 
\family typewriter
classicthesis-config.tex:
\family default

